text: Ronald Joseph "Ron" Mulock (11 January 1930 â€“ 5 September 2014) was an Australian politician and a member of the New South Wales Legislative Assembly. He served as the 10th Deputy Premier of New South Wales serving from 10 February 1984 through 25 March 1988. Mulock died in Sydney, Australia on 5 September 2014 at the age of 84.Former Deputy Premier, Penrith Panthers club patron and life member Ron Mulock has died, The Daily Telegraph, 5 September 2014. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Australian Labor Party politicians Category:Politicians from Sydney
